<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 09 at 12:35PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...BRIEF HEAVY SNOW RATES EXPECTED...
Steady snowfall is spreading southwest to northeast across the
region as temperatures remain in the mid 20s to low 30s. Snow may
initially be moderate to heavy and result in light accumulations
of up to an inch on roads and other surfaces causing slick travel
conditions. As temperatures continue to warm through the
afternoon, snow will transition to rain at lower elevations by
this evening, and at higher elevations by early tonight.</description>
